<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="65" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1792,2036]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1792,1817]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
A 
<taxonomicName box="[356,453,1794,1817]" class="Insecta" family="Calopterygidae" genus="Matrona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[356,453,1794,1817]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Matrona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species with reddish-brown wings, lacking any milky coloured reticulation at the wing bases of the male; apical 
<number box="[439,449,1831,1855]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[460,474,1831,1855]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" value="3.0">3</number>
rd of male fore wing subhyaline. Posclypeus metallic green. Ventral side of the apical segments of abdomen a conspicuous pale olive yellow.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="67" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1792,2036]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1437,151,825]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="67" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,432,1903,1928]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Description of male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[447,517,1903,1927]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 2" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1960,1983]" captionTargetBox="[325,1265,196,1924]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[297,1286,193,1947]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 2. Matrona taoi sp. nov., damselflies photographed in the field in Xuan Son by Phan Quoc Toan on 15 December 2010. 1) male; 2) female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203454/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">
Figs 
<number box="[503,517,1903,1927]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" value="1.3">1</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[532,546,1903,1927]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1726,1749]" captionTargetBox="[234,1309,228,1672]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[187,1399,193,1705]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 4. Matrona taoi sp. nov. 3) habitus of paratype male (right hind wing incomplete at base)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203455/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">3</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis box="[569,630,1904,1928]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Head</emphasis>
: Labium olive yellow, the lateral lobes black at tips. Labrum black with an olive yellow median band, narrowed in the middle; in older specimens the yellow colour reduced to two separate spots. Base of mandibles largely yellow. Anteclypeus black with an obscure yellow spot in the middle. Postclypeus shining metallic green. Frons and upper surface of head black with obscure metallic green sheen. Genae black. Antennae dark, with a yellowish stripe on pedicel. 
<emphasis box="[808,922,1805,1829]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">Prothorax</emphasis>
dark metallic green. 
<emphasis box="[1165,1279,1805,1829]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">Synthorax</emphasis>
dark metallic green. Pale yellow portions are restricted to the level anterior to stigma and around metepimeron (
<figureCitation box="[1265,1335,1841,1865]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1726,1749]" captionTargetBox="[234,1309,228,1672]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[187,1399,193,1705]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 4. Matrona taoi sp. nov. 3) habitus of paratype male (right hind wing incomplete at base)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203455/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">
Fig. 
<number box="[1319,1335,1841,1865]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
). Underside of synthorax largely pale yellow. 
<emphasis box="[575,628,1878,1901]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">Legs</emphasis>
: Coxae pale yellow with black markings on pro- and mesothoracic legs. Femora black with flexor surface partly pale in younger specimens, more markedly so in meso- and metathoracic legs. Tibiae black; meso- and metathoracic tibiae moderately curved (
<figureCitation box="[938,1006,1949,1973]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1726,1749]" captionTargetBox="[234,1309,228,1672]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[187,1399,193,1705]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 4. Matrona taoi sp. nov. 3) habitus of paratype male (right hind wing incomplete at base)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203455/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">
Fig. 
<number box="[991,1006,1949,1973]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis box="[1029,1096,1950,1973]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">Wings</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1114,1181,1949,1973]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1738,1761]" captionTargetBox="[309,1245,226,1681]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[309,1277,193,1717]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 6. Matrona taoi sp. nov. 5) wings of paratype male; 6) wings of paratype female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203456/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">
Fig. 
<number box="[1167,1181,1949,1973]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
) largely brownish, the apical 
<number box="[227,237,1988,2012]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[248,262,1988,2012]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="3.0">3</number>
rd of fore wing subhyaline; in hind wing the apical part slightly more hyaline than base; this difference less marked than in fore wing. In hind wing lower half darker in middle section of wing. Venation dark violet red. Reticulation sparse for genus, best seen in number of intercalary veins and density of crossveins in the area defined by CuP and wing border (
<figureCitation box="[442,509,223,247]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1660,1683]" captionTargetBox="[184,1398,898,1659]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,829,1698]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 7. Matrona taoi sp. nov. paratype male; venation at hind wing base." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203457/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
Fig. 
<number box="[494,509,223,247]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
) and in wing tip. Only 
<number box="[772,816,223,247]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="2.0" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.0">1–3</number>
, partly reticulated, crossveins in median space. Cubital space with 
<number box="[276,346,260,284]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="18.5" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="17.0">17–20</number>
crossveins in fore wing, 
<quantity box="[627,726,260,284]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.699" metricValueMax="5.08" metricValueMin="4.318" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" unit="in" value="18.5" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="17.0">17–20 in</quantity>
hind wing (in 
<typeStatus box="[889,987,260,284]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">holotype</typeStatus>
<number box="[994,1022,260,284]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="20.0">20</number>
crossveins in all wings). Quadrangle with 
<number box="[208,278,295,319]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="15.5" valueMax="18.0" valueMin="13.0">13–18</number>
crossveins in fore wing, 
<quantity box="[564,664,295,319]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.318" metricValueMax="5.08" metricValueMin="3.556" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" unit="in" value="17.0" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="14.0">14–20 in</quantity>
hind wing (in 
<typeStatus box="[832,930,295,319]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">holotype</typeStatus>
<number box="[938,965,295,319]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="15.0">15</number>
– 
<number box="[981,1008,295,319]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="13.0">13</number>
and 
<number box="[1064,1092,295,319]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="18.0">18</number>
– 
<number box="[1108,1136,295,319]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="18.0">18</number>
, respectively). Antenodals (in first row) number 
<quantity box="[404,505,332,356]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1938" metricValueMax="1.3462" metricValueMin="1.0413999999999999" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" unit="in" value="47.0" valueMax="53.0" valueMin="41.0">41–53 in</quantity>
fore wing and 
<quantity box="[684,786,332,356]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0668" metricValueMax="1.2192" metricValueMin="0.9144" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" unit="in" value="42.0" valueMax="48.0" valueMin="36.0">36–48 in</quantity>
hind wing (in 
<typeStatus box="[960,1058,332,356]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">holotype</typeStatus>
<number box="[1068,1095,332,356]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="41.0">41</number>
– 
<number box="[1110,1137,332,356]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="41.0">41</number>
and 
<number box="[1197,1225,332,356]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="38.0">38</number>
– 
<number box="[1241,1270,332,356]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="36.0">36</number>
, respectively). Arculus (Arc) situated at the level of the fifth antenodal. Pterostigma absent in both wings. 
<emphasis box="[1180,1286,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">Abdomen</emphasis>
metallic bluish-green dorsally and laterally; the lower half of side of S 
<number box="[799,828,404,428]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="10.0">10</number>
yellow (
<figureCitation box="[925,993,404,428]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1726,1749]" captionTargetBox="[234,1309,228,1672]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[187,1399,193,1705]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 4. Matrona taoi sp. nov. 3) habitus of paratype male (right hind wing incomplete at base)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203455/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
Fig. 
<number box="[977,993,404,428]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
). Ventral side of S 
<number box="[1199,1210,404,428]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="1.0">1</number>
-S 
<number box="[1236,1251,404,428]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="5.0">5</number>
blackish brown, S 
<number box="[166,203,439,463]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="6.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="6.0">6-7</number>
obscurely pale yellow and S 
<number box="[530,543,439,463]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="8.0">8</number>
-S 
<number box="[567,597,439,463]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="10.0">10</number>
conspicuous pale olive yellow (
<figureCitation box="[960,1032,439,463]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 2" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1960,1983]" captionTargetBox="[325,1265,196,1924]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[297,1286,193,1947]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 2. Matrona taoi sp. nov., damselflies photographed in the field in Xuan Son by Phan Quoc Toan on 15 December 2010. 1) male; 2) female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203454/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
Figs 
<number box="[1018,1032,439,463]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="1.3">1</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1047,1062,439,463]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1726,1749]" captionTargetBox="[234,1309,228,1672]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[187,1399,193,1705]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 4. Matrona taoi sp. nov. 3) habitus of paratype male (right hind wing incomplete at base)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203455/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">3</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis box="[1084,1279,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">Anal appendages</emphasis>
of the typical shape for the genus: cercus wholly black, bearing a row of small spines laterally; paraproct more than half of the length of cercus, black at tip, yellow laterally and ventrally.
</paragraph>
<caption box="[151,1116,1738,1761]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203456/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" targetBox="[309,1245,226,1681]" targetPageId="3">
